com.cloudera.labs.envelope.component

Interface Component

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    BatchInput, BulkOutput, BulkPlanner, DatasetRule, Deriver, Input, Output, Planner, RandomOutput, RandomPlanner, Repetition, RowRule, StreamInput, Task, TimeModel, Translator<K,V>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractRepetition, AppendPlanner, AvroTranslator, BitemporalHistoryPlanner, CheckForNullsRowRule, CheckSchemaDatasetRule, ConfigurablePartitioner, CountDatasetRule, DataQualityDeriver, DatasetRowRuleWrapper, DeletePlanner, DelimitedTranslator, DistinctDeriver, EnumRowRule, EventTimeHistoryPlanner, EventTimeUpsertPlanner, ExcludeDeriver, FileSystemInput, FileSystemOutput, FIXInput, FlagFileRepetition, HBaseOutput, HiveInput, HiveOutput, InListDeriver, JdbcInput, JdbcOutput, KafkaInput, KafkaOutput, KuduInput, KuduOutput, KVPTranslator, LogOutput, LongMillisTimeModel, MorphlineDeriver, MorphlineTranslator, NanosWithSeqNumTimeModel, NestDeriver, OverwritePlanner, PassthroughDeriver, PivotDeriver, ProtobufTranslator, RangeRowRule, RawBinaryTranslator, RawStringTranslator, RegexRowRule, ScheduledRepetition, SelectDeriver, SQLDeriver, StringDateTimeModel, StringDatetimeTimeModel, SystemTimeUpsertPlanner, TimestampTimeModel, UUIDPartitioner, ZooKeeperOutput

    public interface Component
    An Envelope component is a class that can insert functionality into an Envelope pipeline, such as an input, or a deriver, or a task. Envelope exposes interface APIs for components to be implemented with. Those interfaces will extend this Component interface. Envelope provides some built-in components. Pipelines can also provide their own plugins that implement the corresponding component APIs.
